[location trigger] The players enter the tavern.
[npc trigger] Joe greets the players warmly.
[player]: Hi there, Joe! How's business today?
[joe_tavernier]: Business is as grim as ever, lass. The sea monsters keep folks on edge. But a bit of ale might just cheer things up. What brings you to the Rusty Anchor tonight?
[player]: This tavern has such a warm atmosphere. You must take great pride in running it!
[joe_tavernier]: Ah, thanks for the compliment. Keeping this place running is more about necessity than pride. But a cozy corner and good ale do help. What brings you to seek out my warmth tonight?
[player]: I've heard you're one of the most knowledgeable folks in town. How long have you been working here?
[joe_tavernier]: Tavern life, eh? I've been at this for twenty years now. Lost my crew to a sea monster and ended up here. Figured if there's one place where I can learn about those damn beasts, it's the Rusty Anchor.
[player]: You seem like someone who knows all the interesting stories around here.
[joe_tavernier]: Well, the world throws its share of crap at you, and you end up learning a few things along the way. So, what's on your mind? Got a story to share or just looking for some gossip?
[player]: I really appreciate your hospitality. Say, I'm curious about something... have you ever heard tales of any hidden treasures around these parts?
[joe_tavernier]: Tales of treasure are as common as salt in this old port. But don't go thinking too much of it. Most of the stories end up being just thatâ€”stories. If there's anything here, I'd bet it's locked away in some forgotten cellar or behind a secret door.

Now, if you're really interested, why not take a look around? The tavern cellar might have something interesting down there. Care to give it a peek with me?
[player]: I'm actually seeking a treasure. Given how helpful you've been, I was wondering if you might know anything about it?
[joe_tavernier]: *Grumbles* If I knew for sure where the treasure was, you'd probably be the last one to hear about it. But I do have my ways... You see, in the cellar, there's a locked door that no one has opened in years. It might lead somewhere interesting. Care to check it out with me?